Article 1 - Definitions

1.1 "Software" refers to the software products developed and provided by Hefei 
    Muleiwu(Mliev) Information Technology Co., Ltd. (hereinafter "the Company"), 
    including but not limited to source code, object code, documentation, 
    interface designs, and related materials.
1.2 "You" refers to any individual or organization that accepts the terms of 
    this Agreement.
1.3 "Commercial Use" refers to any use for profit or in a commercial environment.
1.4 "Non-Commercial Use" refers to personal learning, research, testing, and 
    other non-profit uses.

Article 2 - License Grant

2.1 Subject to full compliance with this Agreement, the Company grants You the 
    following rights:
    a) To use the Software free of charge for non-commercial or commercial purposes;
    b) To modify the Software source code or interface within the scope permitted 
       by this Agreement to meet Your needs;
    c) To use the Software to build and operate Your websites or applications.

2.2 You own all content in websites or applications built using the Software and 
    shall independently assume all review obligations and legal responsibilities.

Article 3 - Restrictions

3.1 You shall not rent, sell, pledge, or sublicense the Software or any 
    associated authorization.

3.2 Regardless of purpose, modification, or degree of modification, as long as 
    the Software or any part thereof is used, without written permission from 
    the Company, You must retain copyright notices (including but not limited to 
    "Powered by" marks and links to https://www.mliev.com/) and shall not remove, 
    modify, or replace them.

3.3 It is prohibited to develop any derivative versions, modified versions, or 
    third-party versions based on the Software or any part thereof for 
    redistribution.

3.4 It is prohibited to reverse engineer, disassemble, decompile, or otherwise 
    attempt to derive the source code of the Software (except where source code 
    is provided by the Company).

Article 4 - Compliance Requirements

4.1 You must comply with all applicable laws and regulations of the People's 
    Republic of China and Your jurisdiction.

4.2 It is strictly prohibited to use the Software for any illegal or unlawful 
    activities, including but not limited to:
    a) Infringing upon intellectual property rights, privacy rights, or other 
       legitimate rights of others;
    b) Distributing illegal information, harmful content, or spam;
    c) Engaging in fraud, money laundering, or other criminal activities;
    d) Violating data protection regulations or collecting/using personal 
       information without authorization;
    e) Any other activities that violate laws, regulations, or public morals.

4.3 You shall bear all legal liabilities and consequences arising from Your 
    violation of this Article, which shall have no relation to the Company. 
    If such violation causes losses to the Company or third parties, You shall 
    bear full compensation liability.

Article 5 - Disclaimer

5.1 THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR 
    IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS 
    FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.

5.2 The Company shall not be liable for:
    a) Any direct, indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages that 
       may arise from use of the Software;
    b) Service interruptions caused by force majeure (including but not limited 
       to natural disasters, war, government actions);
    c) Losses caused by factors beyond the Company's control, such as hacker 
       attacks, virus intrusions, or system failures;
    d) Any content in websites or applications built using the Software and any 
       resulting liabilities.

5.3 The Company reserves the right to modify, suspend, or terminate the Software 
    and related services at any time without prior notice.

Article 6 - Termination

6.1 If You violate any term of this Agreement, Your license shall automatically 
    terminate, and the Company may require You to:
    a) Immediately cease using the Software;
    b) Delete all copies of the Software;
    c) Compensate the Company for all losses caused by Your breach.

6.2 The Company reserves the right to pursue legal action.

Article 7 - Governing Law and Dispute Resolution

7.1 The formation, validity, interpretation, performance, and dispute resolution 
    of this Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the People's Republic 
    of China.

7.2 Any disputes arising from this Agreement shall first be resolved through 
    friendly negotiation. If negotiation fails, either party may file a lawsuit 
    with a court of competent jurisdiction where the Company is located.

Article 8 - Miscellaneous

8.1 This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between You and the Company 
    regarding the use of the Software.

8.2 The Company reserves the right to modify this Agreement at any time. Modified 
